---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const posts = [
  {
    slug: 'discount-ceiling',
    title: 'Why your discount structure is quietly telling customers to order less',
    topic: 'Subscription economics',
    length: '8 min read',
    featured: true,
    desc: 'Most quantity-based discount schemes have a ceiling problem nobody notices until you map it in a spreadsheet. The moment your discount stops growing with order size, you\'ve accidentally trained your best customers to stop at the wrong number.',
    outline: [
      'The discount ceiling problem — what it is and why it\'s invisible',
      'How to audit your own discount logic with a simple spreadsheet model',
      'What "honoring the per-unit price" actually means in practice',
      'The psychological signal your current structure is sending customers',
      'How to restructure without alienating your existing subscriber base',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'se-role',
    title: 'The SE role nobody describes accurately in a job posting',
    topic: 'Sales engineering',
    length: '6 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'Job descriptions for sales engineers oscillate between "technically deep" and "great communicator" without ever explaining what it actually feels like to hold both simultaneously under pressure.',
    outline: [
      'What the job description says vs. what Tuesday actually looks like',
      'The moment you realize you\'re a translator, not a technologist',
      'Why the best SEs think in business outcomes first, features second',
      'How to know if you\'re cut out for it (honest version)',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'churn-product-problem',
    title: 'Churn is a product problem wearing a retention costume',
    topic: 'Subscription economics',
    length: '7 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'Most subscription businesses treat churn as a retention problem to be solved with better cancellation flows and win-back emails. Some of it is. But the churn that actually kills you is a product problem.',
    outline: [
      'The two types of churn and why only one responds to retention tactics',
      'How to tell which type you have by looking at cancellation timing',
      'What "product-market fit for subscriptions" actually means',
      'The retention metrics that matter vs. the ones that look good in a deck',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'chairlifts',
    title: 'What a year fixing chairlifts taught me about systems thinking',
    topic: 'Career & personal growth',
    length: '5 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'I spent a season as a lift operator and mechanic at Beaver Creek — a deliberate career detour that looked like a step back and turned out to be the most useful year of my professional development.',
    outline: [
      'Why I left a recruiting career to fix machinery at altitude',
      'What mechanical systems teach you that software systems don\'t',
      'The clarity that only comes from stepping fully off the treadmill',
      'How I think about deliberate career pivots now',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'cosell-coordination',
    title: 'Co-selling is a coordination problem, not a relationship problem',
    topic: 'Business strategy',
    length: '6 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'Most co-sell advice focuses on building strong partner relationships. That matters. But the deals that stall don\'t stall because the relationship is bad — they stall because two teams showed up to a merchant call with different answers.',
    outline: [
      'Why vendor misalignment in front of a merchant is so expensive',
      'The pre-call alignment habit that changes everything',
      'How to handle genuine disagreements between partner teams',
      'What "one voice" actually looks like in a multi-vendor deal',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'colorful-resume',
    title: 'The colorful resume advantage',
    topic: 'Career & personal growth',
    length: '5 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'I\'ve worked in government software sales, technical recruiting, ski lift mechanics, point-of-sale support, commercial construction project management, and subscription e-commerce. The non-linear path used to feel like something to explain away.',
    outline: [
      'Why the through-line only becomes visible looking backward',
      'What each "detour" actually gave me that the straight path wouldn\'t have',
      'How non-linear experience creates pattern recognition linear careers miss',
      'The case for trusting the detour while you\'re still in it',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'aov-vanity',
    title: 'AOV is a vanity metric until you understand what drives it',
    topic: 'Product & market analysis',
    length: '7 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'Average order value is one of the most cited subscription metrics and one of the least understood. A rising AOV can mean your customers are buying more — or that your lower-value customers churned.',
    outline: [
      'The two AOV stories that look identical in a dashboard',
      'How to segment AOV by cohort to see what\'s actually happening',
      'The relationship between AOV, LTV, and subscription frequency',
      'What a healthy AOV trend actually looks like',
    ],
  },
  {
    slug: 'subscription-harder',
    title: 'Why subscription commerce is harder than it looks from the outside',
    topic: 'Tech observations',
    length: '8 min read',
    featured: false,
    desc: 'Everyone has noticed that subscription brands make it easy to sign up and hard to cancel. But the technical and operational complexity underneath a well-run subscription program is genuinely underappreciated.',
    outline: [
      'What "just add a subscribe and save button" actually involves',
      'The payment infrastructure layer most merchants don\'t think about until it breaks',
      'Why migration between subscription platforms is so expensive and risky',
      'What good subscription infrastructure actually looks like from the inside',
    ],
  },
];

const featured = posts.find(p => p.featured);
const rest = posts.filter(p => !p.featured);

const topics = ['All', 'Subscription economics', 'Sales engineering', 'Business strategy', 'Career & personal growth', 'Tech observations', 'Product & market analysis'];
---

<BaseLayout title="Writing — JWM" activePage="writing">

  <header class="page-header grid-overlay">
    <p class="eyebrow">Essays &amp; observations</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">Writing</h1>
    <p class="page-desc">Short and medium-length posts on subscription economics, sales engineering, business strategy, and the career stuff nobody talks about honestly enough.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="filter-bar">
    <span class="filter-label">Filter</span>
    {topics.map((t, i) => (
      <button class:list={['filter-btn', { active: i === 0 }]}>{t}</button>
    ))}
  </div>

  <!-- Featured post -->
  {featured && (
    <div class="featured-post">
      <div class="featured-left">
        <p class="featured-eyebrow">
          Featured <span class="featured-tag">— {featured.topic} · {featured.length}</span>
        </p>
        <h2 class="featured-title">{featured.title}</h2>
        <p class="featured-desc">{featured.desc}</p>
        <span class="featured-cta">Read post →</span>
      </div>
      <div class="featured-outline">
        <p class="outline-label">Post outline</p>
        {featured.outline.map((item, i) => (
          <div class="outline-item">
            <span class="outline-num">0{i + 1}</span>
            {item}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  <!-- Posts grid -->
  <div class="posts-grid">
    {rest.map((post, i) => (
      <div class:list={['post-card', { 'post-card--wide': i === rest.length - 1 && rest.length % 2 !== 0 }]}>
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span class="post-topic">{post.topic}</span>
          <span class="post-dot"></span>
          <span class="post-length">{post.length}</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="post-title">{post.title}</h3>
        <p class="post-desc">{post.desc}</p>
        <div class="post-outline">
          {post.outline.map(item => (
            <div class="post-outline-item">
              <span class="post-outline-dash">—</span>
              {item}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <span class="post-cta">Read post →</span>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="topics-footer">
    <p class="topics-label mono-label">What I write about</p>
    <p class="topics-desc">These posts sit at the intersection of <strong>subscription economics, sales engineering craft, and business strategy</strong> — with occasional detours into career thinking and tech observations. Nothing is written to be safe or generic. Posts are short to medium length — long enough to be useful, short enough to finish on a lunch break.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="subscribe-section">
    <div>
      <h2 class="subscribe-heading">New posts, <em>when they're ready.</em></h2>
      <p class="subscribe-sub">No cadence, no newsletter fluff. Just a heads-up when something new goes up that's worth reading.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="subscribe-action">
      <a href="mailto:jmuhlenberg16@yahoo.com" class="btn-primary">Get notified</a>
      <p class="subscribe-note">No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding: 10rem 3rem 5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .page-desc { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 520px; }

  /* Filter bar */
  .filter-bar {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .filter-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-right: 0.5rem; }
  .filter-btn {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem; cursor: pointer; transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s; background: none;
  }
  .filter-btn:hover { color: var(--text-primary); border-color: var(--border-mid); }
  .filter-btn.active { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent-border); background: rgba(200,240,84,0.04); }

  /* Featured post */
  .featured-post {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 380px;
    gap: 5rem; align-items: start;
    transition: background 0.25s; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .featured-post:hover { background: var(--surface); }
  .featured-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;
  }
  .featured-tag { color: var(--text-muted); }
  .featured-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .featured-desc { font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 2rem; max-width: 520px; }
  .featured-cta { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); }

  .featured-outline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .outline-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--surface-2); }
  .outline-item {
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text-secondary);
    display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline;
  }
  .outline-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .outline-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; color: var(--accent); flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* Posts grid */
  .posts-grid {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5px; background: var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .post-card {
    background: var(--surface); padding: 2.5rem;
    cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.2s;
    position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .post-card--wide { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
  .post-card::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 3px; height: 0; background: var(--accent);
    transition: height 0.3s ease;
  }
  .post-card:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .post-card:hover::before { height: 100%; }

  .post-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .post-topic { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); }
  .post-length { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .post-dot { width: 3px; height: 3px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--border-mid); }

  .post-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .post-desc { font-size: 0.83rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  .post-outline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .post-outline-item { font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; align-items: baseline; }
  .post-outline-dash { color: var(--accent); flex-shrink: 0; font-size: 0.7rem; }
  .post-cta { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); }

  /* Topics footer */
  .topics-footer {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start;
  }
  .topics-label { padding-top: 0.3rem; }
  .topics-desc { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .topics-desc strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  /* Subscribe */
  .subscribe-section {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 5rem 3rem;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 4rem; align-items: center;
  }
  .subscribe-heading { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); line-height: 1.15; }
  .subscribe-heading em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .subscribe-sub { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1rem; max-width: 440px; }
  .subscribe-action { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-end; }
  .subscribe-note { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); text-align: right; }
</style>